      "full_name": "FSE “KGKPZ”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "FSE Kazan State-Owned Gunpowder Plant is a Russian chemical plant that produces a variety of pyroxylin powders and charges for almost all types of weapons. The plant manufactures 5.45-14.5 mm caliber cartridges for rifles (Kalashnikov assault rifles), grenade launchers charges, propellant charges for naval cannons (AK-100, AK-130 and AK-726) and land artillery of 76 mm to 152 mm caliber (mortars 2S9 and 2S12, howitzers D-20, D-30, ML-20, 2S1, 2S3 and 2S19). The plant produces 115 mm, 122 mm and, most importantly, 125 mm caliber tank ammunition, which is used in the T-64, T-72, T-80 and T-90 tanks of the Russian Armed Forces. FKP KGKPZ supplies ammunition to the Russian Armed Forces and their weapon systems used in Ukraine.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}